-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Carrefour, Spirent Communications   
-- 
-- Fri Oct 10, 2014 04:32AM EDT
-- None



Oct 10 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Carrefour and Spirent Communications, on Friday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Carrefour SA <CARR.PA>: Goldman Sachs raises to neutral from conviction-list sell   * Spirent Communications Plc <SPT.L>: Morgan Stanley raises to equal weight from underweightFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Friday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.   * Balfour Beatty Plc <BALF.L>: Jefferies cuts price target to 164p from 233p; rating hold  * British American Tobacco <BTIJ.J>: Renaissance Capital raises target to 660 rand; hold  * British American Tobacco <BATS.L>: Renaissance Capital raises target to 3750p; rating hold * Carrefour SA <CARR.PA>: Goldman Sachs raises to neutral from conviction-list sell  * Carrefour SA <CARR.PA>: Goldman Sachs removes from pan europe conviction-sell list  * Carrefour SA <CARR.PA>: Goldman Sachs raises price target to 23 euros from 22.4 euros  * Clariant AG <CLN.VX>: JP Morgan cuts target to sfr 20.20 from sfr 20.50; rating overweight * CNH Industrial NV <CNHI.MI>: JP Morgan cuts target to $7.50 from $9; rating underweight  * DIA <DIDA.MC>: JP Morgan cuts target to 4.45 euros from 5.95 euros; rating underweight  * PZU <PZU.WA>: JP Morgan cuts price target to pln 493 from pln 497; rating overweight  * Salamander Energy Plc <SMDR.L>: Jefferies cuts price target to 110p from 260p; rating buy  * Spirent Communications Plc <SPT.L>: Morgan Stanley raises to equal weight from underweight